Description: Wall sherd of East Greek (?) pottery closed vessel;, probably an olpe; polished on the outside; black band painted near top of wall on the outside; inscription cut on exterior, in reserved zone.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of the Dioskouroi (Naukratis), Buried in sand under the west wall of Temenos.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXV, no. 668)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.937)
